EXPLANATION:
The script was developed on Python, Selenium and Behave(BDD). I didn't implement Page Object pattern because It's a simple project, adding more complexity to it would be superfluos and possibily counterproductive. 

STEPS TO EXCECUTE THE TEST CASE:

1-Update your system software: 
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get -y upgrade

2-Install Pip:
sudo apt-get install python-pip

3-Install or upgrade Selenium:
pip install -U selenium

4-Install behave with pip:
pip install behave

5-Config geckodriver:
wget https://github.com/mozilla/geckodriver/releases/download/v0.18.0/geckodriver-v0.18.0-linux64.tar.gz
tar -xvzf geckodriver-v0.18.0-linux64.tar.gz
chmod +x geckodriver
sudo cp geckodriver /usr/local/bin/

6-Clone the following repository: https://github.com/ramiro015/pythonbehave.git

7-Go to features folder

8-Open a terminal

8-Execute the test case:
behave google.feature
